OL,3,CDeputy Reform leader quit because role
OL,4,Cwas 'very demanding'
OL,6,FThe leader of Leicestershire County
OL,7,FCouncil has said his 22-year-old
OL,8,Fdeputy stood down because he was
OL,9,F"uncomfortable" in the role and found
OL,10,Fit "very demanding".
OL,12,FCouncillor Dan Harrison, who heads the
OL,13,FReform UK administration, told ITV
OL,14,FNews Central that Joseph Boam came to
OL,15,Fhim directly with concerns about the
OL,16,Fpressures of the job.
OL,18,F"He spoke about some of the
OL,19,Fdifficulties and I accelerated it."
