OL,6,FMr Harrison said. "He was
OL,7,Funcomfortable with it and found it
OL,8,Fvery demanding.There's nothing wrong
OL,9,Fin that."
OL,11,FCllr Boam, elected in May to represent
OL,12,FWhitwick in North West Leicestershire,
OL,13,Fhad also been appointed cabinet lead
OL,14,Fmember for adult social care and
OL,15,Fcommunities - one of the council's
OL,16,Flargest portfolios. He no longer holds
OL,17,Feither position.
OL,19,FAsked whether it had been a mistake to
OL,20,Fgive him such a senior role, Mr
OL,21,FHarrison replied: "Definitely not."
