OL,3,CDeputy Reform leader quit because role
OL,4,Cwas 'very demanding'
OL,6,FCllr Smith criticised Mr Harrison's
OL,7,Fdecision to place huge budgets in the
OL,8,Fhands of "inexperienced" councillors.
OL,9,F"For some reason, Mr Harrison chose a
OL,10,F19-year-old... to run the council's
OL,11,Fbiggest department, #330 million
OL,12,Fchildren and families.
OL,14,FAnd he put a 22-year-old in charge of
OL,15,Fthe second biggest. So you're looking
OL,16,Fat three-quarters of the entire
OL,17,Fcouncil budget given to two young
OL,18,Fpeople with no previous experience.
OL,19,FThat, to me, says a lot about poor
OL,20,Fleadership."
